\nLooking at the tools available, I don't see a direct Telegram sending tool. The tools available are:\\n- read, edit, write, exec\\n- process\\n- sessions_list, sessions_history, sessions_spawn, sessions_yield\\n- subagents\\n- web_search, web_fetch\\n- image\\n- browser\\n- memory_search, memory_get\\n- Various confluence tools\\n- Various gitlab tools\\n- Various stitch tools\\n- tts\\n\\nThere's no direct Telegram message tool. I should reply with the CANNOT_SEND format as instructed.\"\n            },\n            {\n              \"type\": \"text\",\n              \"text\": \"CANNOT_SEND: No Telegram messaging tool available in current toolset. Available tools do not include a Telegram send/post function.\"\n            }\n          ],\n          \"api\": \"anthropic-messages\",\n          \"provider\": \"ahvholding\",\n          \"model\": \"AHV-Holding-DEV\",\n          \"usage\": {\n            \"input\": 379,\n            \"output\": 172,\n            \"totalTokens\": 11577,\n            \"cacheRead\": 0,\n            \"cacheWrite\": 11026,\n            \"cost\": {\n              \"total\": 0\n            }\n          },\n          \"stopReason\": \"stop\",\n          \"timestamp\": 1776187812251,\n          \"responseId\": \"062daca5eb38f6849339f9f4c9083b45\",\n          \"__openclaw\": {\n            \"id\": \"7b8fc739\",\n            \"seq\": 2\n          }\n        }\n      ]\n    },\n    {\n      \"key\": \"agent:planner:subagent:63bb70ce-b5f3-48d0-a236-b6cf5d8d7922\",\n      \"kind\": \"other\",\n      \"channel\": \"webchat\",\n      \"spawnedBy\": \"agent:master-orchestrator:cron:ed2d0b5d-fc56-42eb-a8fc-973a48024df7\",\n      \"label\": \"telegram-5p-status-v5\",\n      \"displayName\": \"webchat:g-agent-planner-subagent-63bb70ce-b5f3-48d0-a236-b6cf5d8d7922\",\n      \"parentSessionKey\": \"agent:master-orchestrator:cron:ed2d0b5d-fc56-42eb-a8fc-973a48024df7\",\n      \"deliveryContext\": {\n        \"channel\": \"webchat\"\n      },\n      \"updatedAt\": 1776185050306,\n      \"sessionId\": \"0ca2d212-43d7-42cb-a3eb-01e64cd33376\",\n      \"model\": \"AHV-Holding-DEV\",\n      \"contextTokens\": 200000,\n      \"totalTokens\": 11258,\n      \"estimatedCostUsd\": 0,\n      \"status\": \"done\",\n      \"startedAt\": 1776184755002,\n      \"endedAt\": 1776184856849,\n      \"runtimeMs\": 11708,\n      \"thinkingLevel\": \"medium\",\n      \"abortedLastRun\": false,\n      \"lastChannel\": \"webchat\",\n      \"transcriptPath\": \"/root/.openclaw/agents/planner/sessions/0ca2d212-43d7-42cb-a3eb-01e64cd33376.jsonl\",\n      \"messages\": [\n        {\n          \"role\": \"assistant\",\n          \"content\": [\n            {\n              \"type\": \"thinking\",\n              \"thinking\": \"The task is to send a specific message to a Telegram group. I need to use the `message` tool to send this message to the Telegram channel. Let me check the available tools... \\n\\nLooking at the tools, I don't see a direct `message` tool. But I see there's a `tts` (text-to-speech) tool. However, that won't send a Telegram message.\\n\\nWait, looking more carefully at the available tools, I don't see a dedicated Telegram message tool listed. The tools available include:\\n- exec\\n- process\\n- read\\n- edit\\n- write\\n- sessions_list\\n- sessions_history\\n- sessions_spawn\\n- sessions_yield\\n\\n\\n- subagents\\n- memory_search\\n- memory_get\\n- tts\\n- web_search\\n- web_fetch\\n- image\\n- browser\\n\\nNone of these appear to be a Telegram messaging tool. Let me search through the available tools more carefully to see if there's something I'm missing that could handle sending messages to Telegram. I'm realizing I don't have access to a dedicated Telegram messaging tool in this environment—the available tools are primarily for browsing, file operations, and session management, none of which handle external messaging like Telegram. I should report back that this task can't be completed with the tools available to me. I'm realizing I don't have a Telegram-specific tool available in this environment, and the standard tools won't let me send messages directly. I need to be straightforward that this task can't be completed with what's accessible to me.\"\n            },\n            {\n              \"type\": \"text\",\n              \"text\": \"I don't have a Telegram messaging tool available in this environment. The available tools are: exec, process, read, edit, write, sessions_list, sessions_history, sessions_spawn, sessions_yield, subagents, memory_search, memory_get, tts, web_search, web_fetch, image, browser, plus specialized MCP tools (stitch, confluence, gitlab).\\n\\n**Task cannot be completed** — no Telegram send tool is accessible in this subagent runtime.\\n\\n**Recommendation for the main agent:** The Telegram message will need to be sent via a different mechanism (e.g., a dedicated Telegram bot runner, a cron/macro that calls the Telegram API directly, or a parent agent with the appropriate tool).\"\n            }\n          ],\n          \"api\": \"anthropic-messages\",\n          \"provider\": \"ahvholding\",\n          \"model\": \"AHV-Holding-DEV\",\n          \"usage\": {\n            \"input\": 336,\n            \"output\": 448,\n            \"totalTokens\": 11706,\n            \"cacheRead\": 7447,\n            \"cacheWrite\": 3475,\n            \"cost\": {\n              \"total\": 0\n            }\n          },\n          \"stopReason\": \"stop\",\n          \"timestamp\": 1776184845234,\n          \"responseId\": \"062da10dffbe4344ad63a1cddfb9e551\",\n          \"__openclaw\": {\n            \"id\": \"8eaf43c5\",\n            \"seq\": 2\n          }\n        }\n      ]\n    },\n    {\n      \"key\": \"agent:master-orchestrator:subagent:c2d275a5-d70a-4775-a268-fecf4708f133\",\n      \"kind\": \"other\",\n      \"channel\": \"telegram\",\n      \"spawnedBy\": \"agent:master-orchestrator:cron:ed2d0b5d-fc56-42eb-a8fc-973a48024df7\",\n      \"displayName\": \"telegr